title: Search the Armed Forces Memorial roll of honour

heading_context: Search the Armed Forces Memorial roll of honour
chunks.html_content:
You can search the Armed Forces Memorial roll of honour to see if someone’s listed on it.

The Memorial commemorates members of the armed forces who died while in service either:

  • on or after 1 January 1948
  • in Palestine between 1945 and 1947

Entries on the roll of honour database include:

  • rank
  • type of service
  • regiment or corps
  • date of death
  • burial place, if known
  • whether someone’s name is on the Memorial in the National Memorial Arboretum
